text: Litoria sauroni is a tree frog from Papua New Guinea. Scientists have only seen it in the Kikori Integrate Conservation and Development Project area. Different scientists disagree about whether this frog should be in the genus Litoria or Nyctimystes. This frog has red-and-black eyes and pads, called nuptial pads, on its front feet. ==References== Category:Frogs of Oceania
title: Litoria sauroni
